Gene Expression Analysis Platform

Prerequisites - R and Python3, with the following packages:

R Packages (in requirements.R) - yaml, tidyverse, BiocManager, ggpubr

BiocManager packages (in requirements.R) - BiocParallel, affycoretools, affyPLM, hgu133plus2.db, qvalue, sva

Python3 packages (all in webapp/requirements.txt):
Required - Flask, Flask-Session, PyYAML, gunicorn
Optional/for development (uncomment lines in requirements.txt) - virtualenv, jupyterlab, pandas, numpy

Instructions to set up and start the web app (on a linux machine with R and Python3 installed):
1. Clone this repo
git clone git@github.com:McGuiJames/DGEAP.git

2. Set up
FOR SETTING UP IN A NEW ENVIRONMENT (Install Python3/R packages):
  cd DGEAP
  pip3 install --upgrade pip
  pip3 -r webapp/requirements.txt
  Rscript requirements.R
FOR RUNNING IN A SINGULARITY CONTAINER (with pre-installed Python3/R packages):
  cd DGEAP
  singularity run [path_to_singularity_image]

3. Run the web app (replace xxxx with a port number)
FOR PRODUCTION (run with gunicorn):
  cd webapp
  gunicorn --workers=3 --threads=2 --bind 0.0.0.0:xxxx wsgi:app
  ...or run the server persistently in the background like this:
  nohup gunicorn --workers=3 --threads=2 --bind 0.0.0.0:xxxx wsgi:app &
FOR DEVELOPMENT (run with flask development server):
  export FLASK_APP=app
  cd webapp
  flask run -h 0.0.0.0 -p xxxx
